<HEADLINE> Numbers From Tax Filing Season  </HEADLINE>
By The Associated Press	   Some numbers to keep in mind as Americans finish up
the annual
income tax filing season, which draws to a close at midnight April
17, according to the congressional Joint Economic Committee.
<TEXT>
<P>
   --481. The number of separate Internal Revenue Service tax forms
for individuals and business.
</P>
<P>
   --403. The number of forms in 1990.
</P>
<P>
   --2,840. The number of pages in the tax code.
</P>
<P>
   --1,340. The number of pages in the Bible.
</P>
<P>
   --6.1 billion. How many hours the IRS estimates Americans as a
whole will spend complying with the tax code in 2000.
</P>
<P>
   --$200 billion. The estimated cost of federal tax compliance to
business and individuals.
</P>
<P>
   --110 million. The number of telephone calls the IRS gets from
taxpayers each year.
</P>
<P>
   --73 percent. The percentage of inquiries the IRS was able to
answer correctly in 1999.
</P>
