<HEADLINE> Underwood Says Blacks Shortchanged  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Blair Underwood says the furor over the lack
of minority faces on TV and in films hasn't changed the big picture
much.
</P>
<P>
   Blacks and other minorities still are shortchanged by the big
networks and on the big screen, says the black actor, who plays Dr.
Ben Turner on the CBS show ''City of Angels'' and has a role in the
new film ''Rules of Engagement.''
</P>
<P>
   ''The lack is on the major networks,'' he told the Los Angeles
Times. ''You are saying, UPN, the WB and the cables -- you'll handle
the black audience, and the networks that have the most money,
access and channels will exclude all the people of color. Therein
lies the problem.''
</P>
<P>
   On film, minorities have more representation in independent
productions than in big studio productions ''unless you're a big
name like Sam Jackson or Denzel (Washington),'' he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
